PhysioNet Credentialed Health Data License 1.5.0
=================================================

The CORTEX benchmark distributed on PhysioNet (source/), and the numeric
artifacts shipped alongside this codebase (predictions/, confidence_scores/,
trained_models/), are released under the PhysioNet Credentialed Health Data
License 1.5.0 — the same license under which the source CORAL dataset
(Sushil et al., 2024), EHRNoteQA, and MIMIC-IV are distributed.

Full license text:
https://physionet.org/about/licenses/physionet-credentialed-health-data-license-150/

Summary of obligations:

1. Access requires a credentialed PhysioNet account, completion of CITI human
   subjects research training, and a signed data use agreement.

2. Use is limited to non-commercial research. Commercial use is not permitted.

3. Redistribution to non-credentialed individuals is not permitted.

4. Users must cite the accompanying paper and the source CORAL dataset:
   - Khanmohammadi R et al., Confidence estimation determines safe automation
     of oncology chart review across clinical reasoning complexity tiers,
     2026.
   - Sushil M et al., CORAL: Expert-Curated Oncology Reports to Advance
     Language Model Inference, NEJM AI, 2024.

5. Re-identification attempts on any patient are prohibited.

The accompanying code in this repository (everything outside the data/
directory) is released under the MIT License (see top-level LICENSE).
